= Accordion Blocks

Accordion blocks allow you to create collapsible sections of content.

== Basic Accordion

_-_#accordion1[name="First Section"]
Content for the first accordion section.

_-_#accordion2[name="Second Section"]
Content for the second accordion section.

_-_#accordion3[name="Third Section"]
Content for the third accordion section.

_-_

== Accordion with Multiple Paragraphs

_-_#section1[name="Section One"]
This accordion section has multiple paragraphs.

Here's the second paragraph.

And a third paragraph.

_-_#section2[name="Section Two"]
This is another section.

With its own content.

_-_

== Accordion with Lists

_-_#list-section[name="List Section"]
This section contains a list:

* First item
* Second item
* Third item

_-_#code-section[name="Code Section"]
This section contains code:

[source]
----
function example() {
  return "Hello";
}
----

_-_

== Accordion with Mixed Content

_-_#mixed[name="Mixed Content"]
This accordion has *bold* and _italic_ text.

And a code block:

[source]
----
example code
----

And a list:

* Item one
* Item two

_-_

== Nested Accordions

_-_#parent[name="Parent Section"]
Parent content here.

_-_#child1[name="Child Section 1"]
Child content one.

_-_#child2[name="Child Section 2"]
Child content two.

_-_


